description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the South Locality CMHTs in Trafford.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a dynamic and innovative trust providing an excellent environment in which employees can develop and progress in their career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greater Manchester West Mental Health NHS Foundation Trust provides a wide range of local services to Manchester, Bolton, Salford and Trafford Residents. In addition the Trust provides a number of specialist and secure mental health services supporting Greater Manchester the Northwest and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is ideally situated to support a healthy work / life balance. We are a dynamic and innovative trust providing an excellent environment in which employees can develop and progress in their career. With our Trust Headquarters just 3 miles to the north of Manchester City Centre our employees can also enjoy all of the benefits of excellent transport links, great restaurants, a vibrant night life, three local major Football Clubs, City Centre shops and the Trafford centre all within easy reach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide medical input to the South Trafford Locality (Central and South CMHTs) This is a community based post with daytime cover and on call at the Moorside Unit, Trafford General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JD &amp; PS is currently waiting for Royal College approval. Approved JD &amp; PS will be provided to successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Luis Rojo - Lead Consultant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 0161 746 2685&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: luis.rojo@gmmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
